If you're interviewing for an Application Support Engineer/Azure DevOps role at Accenture supporting banking clients, the interviewer is typically looking for real-world production support scenarios rather than just Azure DevOps features.

Here are some of the most common issues banking companies face and how an Application Support Engineer is expected to handle them.

1. Production Deployment Failure
Scenario

A release to Production fails halfway through, leaving some services updated and others on the old version.

Possible Causes
Pipeline task failure
IIS service not restarted
Database migration failure
Network timeout
Storage account inaccessible
Deployment package corrupted
Troubleshooting
Check Azure DevOps Pipeline logs.
Identify the failed task.
Verify deployment logs on target servers.
Compare deployed artifacts.
Roll back if required.
Redeploy after fixing the issue.
2. Azure DevOps Agent Offline
Scenario

The production deployment cannot start because the self-hosted agent is offline.

Common Causes
Agent service stopped
VM rebooted
Certificate expired
Firewall issue
Agent token expired
Resolution
Verify agent status.
Restart Azure Pipelines Agent service.
Check connectivity to Azure DevOps.
Renew PAT if expired.
Validate firewall rules.
3. Pipeline Stuck in Queue

Very common in banking organizations.

Causes
No available agent
Agent capability mismatch
Concurrency limit reached
Agent disconnected
Resolution
Check Agent Pool
Verify Demands & Capabilities
Increase parallel jobs
Restart agents
